HEADWORD: Countess
<hw>Count"ess</hw> <pr>(kount"?s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Countesses</plw> <pr>(-<?/s)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[F.
<ets>comtesse</ets>. See <er>Count</er> a nobleman.]</ety> <def>The wife
of an earl in the British peerage, or of a count in the Continental
nobility; also, a lady possessed of the same dignity in her own right.
See the Note under <er>Count</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

